The following figure shows how the Bayesian Classifier can be first trained to estimate the Prior and the Class Conditional Gaussian Densities (as a Generative Model) and then using Bayes Rule the Posterior Probabilities for the class labels can be predicted on the new test dataset.

The following figure shows the decision boundaries with the trained classifier on the same 2-D test dataset. As can be seen, since the the covariance matrices of the class conditional Gaussians were not shared (unlike as in the case of Linear Discriminant Analysis), the decision boundaries are quite complex.
